description: QuarkNet Coding Camp 1 is a one-week remote workshop for teachers where you'll learn to code in Python, analyze particle physics data, and practice integrating that into your own curriculum with reformed pedagogy. Along the way, you'll pick up strategies for promoting diversity, equity, and inclusion through your curriculum. We'll meet via Zoom Mon-Fri for a week. Whether you’re a beginner or well-practiced at coding or particle physics, there’s a place for you here.
